{{Wireless embedded system |brand=LUCKIMAGE |model=WiFi Box W1 |fcc_date=08/08/2018 |is_manuf=No |type=wireless camera |fcc_id=2AQPE-W1 |cpu2_model=X6 |expansion_if_types=USB 2.0 (Female Micro-B), |expansion_usb_num=2 |wi1_module_if=soldered to main board |wi1_chip1_brand=Realtek |wi1_chip1_model=RTL8188FTV;REALTEK, 8188FTV, 12152G1, G106B; |wi1_802dot11_protocols=bgn |wi1_txchains=1 |wi1_rxchains=1 |wi1_sstreams=1 |eth_none=true |flags=battery backup, |802dot11_protocols=bgn }} May also be called the MicroEye W1 or MicroEye W2.
Used to allow wireless access to various USB endoscope/otoscope cameras via ''Anyscope'' app on a mobile device. The camera is likely sold separately or bundled.
